<br>
Want a challenge?  Want to fight something friggin nasty without having to go on a raid or fight your way into a huge dungeon just to make it to one spot to find the damn thing is camped anway?  Want to return to an old friend: Everfrost?<br>
<br>
Then your day has come my friend!  That's right! In the caverns below the river in Everfrost lies the Lich Miragul.  Yep, many may know him and most have forgot him.  He is blue to high 40's and low 50's and is one mean mothafucka.  I did start out by saying this was a challenge.  <br>
<br>
Let's look at the reasons for this fun holiday in Halas.<br>
<br>
1. Chae will be 49 soon and her rez makes dying a damn bit more acceptable!  But dying is pessimistic so forget I said that part.<br>
<br>
2.  Nothing poses a threat to us right up to the Lich Bitch himself.  Unless you decide to sit down on the tundra and let an IB skelly beat on you for 5 hours until you expire from boredom.<br>
<br>
3.  When is the last time you have been to Everfrost?  And for that matter when is the last time HH  has pulled together for an outing like this?<br>
<br>
4. Miragul's Robes.....ah...don't mind those....not really important except that I would like the looting rights to the horribly drab things **Eldrias hopes they fall for that one**<br>
<br>
5.  We got enough binders and porters (Surefall Port ring any bells kids?) to make the trip pretty much painless.  We can all bind in Halas and take you all back to where you were bound originally and rebind ya.<br>
<br>
6. Exp.  I sure as hell hope he will give most of us experience.<br>
<br>
7. A new car!  Yep that is right...you may own a new car someday. Just hang in there and save up your money!<br>
<br>
Seriously folks...I think this would be fun to try.  I will not hold back the truth that Miragul is one nasty sumama bitch.  Hell, he is part of the Norrath storyline.  The robes are comparable to my current ones with extra AC and a different look.<br>
<br>
Let's try this folks.  If you don't want to then where has our sense of crazy adventuring gone to?  Of course Mac, Mira, Walli, Ehron, Norco, Fhozie (if he would), Targys, and Dacia are all invited. Why?  Well you are all damn well level 50 or higher that is why.<br>
<br>
Death to the Lich!<br>
